main event: Observer reported seeing 3 unidentified objects in the sky which moved rapidly and changed direction for about 20 minutes.
interesting points: The objects were observed for 20 minutes with no further details or conclusions provided., Misawa RAPCON officers discerned no special pattern in the unidentified targets., The targets were seen on radar but did not converge in any identifiable manner., Radar observations later indicated that the objects were likely electronic phenomena and not weather-related., No photographs or physical evidence were documented for the sighting.
sighted object: three unidentified objects in the sky
witness description: TSgt Sawitz, A/3C Jackson, A/2C Woody, A1C Rupert (Radar Maint)
